<br>
Was in Misty playing a low-level Druid in first-person view.  Cast Flame Lick on the MOB that was beating on me and noticed that the fiery spell effect actually caused a negative image of my field of view -- highlighting MOBs as blank images in the distance, probably due to the way they are rendered.<br>
<br>
Didn't have time to test this further, but it might be interesting to see if this only works for the visible field of view, or if it could be used to see through walls, or whatever.  Also, if it picks up on just visible MOBs or invisible ones.<br>
<br>
If someone has time to check this out, might be interesting to get more data on this. <p>Fwin Peaks <BR>
